# Tailwind CSS Guidelines

## Design Tokens

All design values must be centralized in `tailwind.config.js`:

```javascript
module.exports = {
  theme: {
    colors: {
      primary: '#0066FF',
      secondary: '#FF3366',
    },
    spacing: {
      xs: '0.25rem',
      sm: '0.5rem',
      md: '1rem',
      lg: '1.5rem',
    },
    fontSize: {
      sm: '0.875rem',
      base: '1rem',
      lg: '1.125rem',
      xl: '1.25rem',
    },
  },
};
```

## Reusable Patterns with @apply

Extract repeated patterns into components or utility classes:

### ✅ GOOD - Reusable Patterns

```vue
<!-- FlexCenter.vue -->
<script setup>
defineProps({ gap: { type: String, default: 'gap-4' } });
</script>

<template>
  <div :class="['flex items-center justify-center', gap]">
    <slot />
  </div>
</template>
```

Or in CSS:

```css
/* globals.css */
@layer components {
  .flex-center {
    @apply flex items-center justify-center;
  }
  
  .card-base {
    @apply rounded-lg bg-white shadow-md p-4;
  }
  
  .btn-base {
    @apply px-4 py-2 rounded font-semibold transition-colors;
  }
}
```

## Template Readability

Keep templates readable. Long class strings should be broken into multiple lines or extracted:

### ✅ GOOD - Readable

```vue
<template>
  <button
    :class="[
      'px-4 py-2 rounded font-semibold',
      'transition-colors duration-200',
      variant === 'primary' ? 'bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700' : 'bg-gray-200',
      disabled ? 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed' : 'cursor-pointer'
    ]"
  >
    <slot />
  </button>
</template>
```

### ❌ BAD - Unreadable

```vue
<template>
  <button class="px-4 py-2 rounded font-semibold transition-colors duration-200 bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700 disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed">
    <slot />
  </button>
</template>
```

## Avoid Magic Values

### ✅ GOOD - Use Design Tokens

```vue
<template>
  <div class="p-4 gap-4"><!-- using spacing tokens --></div>
</template>
```

### ❌ BAD - Magic Values

```vue
<template>
  <div class="p-[17px] gap-[18px]"><!-- arbitrary values --></div>
</template>
```

## Avoid Logic in Class Names

Dynamic classes should be in script, not templates:

### ✅ GOOD

```vue
<script setup>
const buttonClass = computed(() => ({
  'bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700': variant === 'primary',
  'bg-gray-200 hover:bg-gray-300': variant === 'secondary',
  'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed': disabled,
}));
</script>

<template>
  <button :class="buttonClass"><slot /></button>
</template>
```

### ❌ BAD

```vue
<template>
  <!-- Logic in template -->
  <button :class="[variant === 'primary' ? 'bg-blue-600' : 'bg-gray-200', disabled && 'opacity-50']">
    <slot />
  </button>
</template>
```
